  & MS House Bill 999. Reducing the Risk, published by ETR Associates, is a school-based, evidence-based abstinence-plus program that teaches students the interpersonal or social skills they can use to abstain or protect themselves from pregnancy, STD \ HIV. Abstinence is presented as the best, safest and most common choice for high school students, but Reducing the Risk also recognizes that some students are sexually active. For this reason, students are given clear guidelines and rationales for using protection during sex. Please Also indicate which keywords best match your program's offerings: You may suggest additional keywords that might be included in a searchable database of providers: ETR Associates Evidence-based curricula Pregnancy prevention, HIV and AIDS prevention, STD prevention Abstinence plus Skills-based trainings Teaching assistance Program evaluation Please provide a sample of program's offerings (e.g. curriculum, training agenda, sample assessment) See Appendix 1 for a Sample Training Agenda and Appendix 2 for the Curriculum Class by Class Outline. \\

